    <Folder>
      <name>Fishing locations</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Alton Baker Canal</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Alton Baker Pond and Canoe Canal are located within Alton Baker Park, one of the most popular and multi-functional parks in Eugene. <br>The park is located on the north bank of the Willamette River just east of the Ferry Street Bridge and Coburg Road. It is accessible by foot or bike from either side of the river via the River Bank Trails. By car you can enter via the Club Road underpass off Coburg Road or from Autzen Stadium off MLK/Centennial. <br>Located with in the park are two ponds and a canal, which can be accessed by rented canoes during the summer months.<br>TROUT STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=ALTON+BAKER+CANAL&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.0817677,44.0566061,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Benson Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4xSfsJ5tyEwblhLDOrnccji0k8CRyovpi74n362YzvMmEdvox2FFvC2Nd8d-opmNkP7DfLiEdRXkJT32iTqZ0MG_Cw6-Gxl7ex_0HXKljnYJb1KiyXcKIY5hVRvohb5z8D7Z34aXlB1ysu-Vxg9coq" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 40-acre lake located in Benson State Park in the Columbia River Gorge. From Portland, head east on I-84, park is located on the south side of the freeway approx. 1/2 mile west of Multnomah Falls.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, white crappie, largemouth bass, brown bullhead<br><br>Benson State Recreation Area (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_147.php)<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=BENSON+LAKE&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4xSfsJ5tyEwblhLDOrnccji0k8CRyovpi74n362YzvMmEdvox2FFvC2Nd8d-opmNkP7DfLiEdRXkJT32iTqZ0MG_Cw6-Gxl7ex_0HXKljnYJb1KiyXcKIY5hVRvohb5z8D7Z34aXlB1ysu-Vxg9coq</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.126072,45.576658,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bethany Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v49KB-6PDo-d4JPilD6UfehTPccouzcKon2198TPy3vDft3hG0jvrP4K564lKv-PHsQCzst-aTR3jj5n9gwsGlN_nzjuNecZRCmFJK-o7PX5Jxr77fj-B2cnrnexdmUXNUhT9NERp1DvXIww07kv-KpWQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 10-acre pond located at Bethany west of Portland. The pond is maintained by Tualatin Hills Park and Rec. (http://www.thprd.org/parks/parkdetail.cfm?id=23) Amenities include picnic tables, restrooms, and a paved, ADA accessible trail.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill, bullhead<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=BETHANY+PD&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
