      <Placemark>
        <name>Blue Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4BwdFjeaXnlVsGlwVt_N07Q2lOv9z-ErOBvw7jrYGvG-lpDu4y1xr0WlvloFZSkKv2uJXEZImA42FUkukfyeo_GTErp-oVg1_ag8XjkL-NmL7ndrxHAv1QT7O8hb0yzz2M6c08FWFvwi4bG7YT" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 64-acre lake located in Blue Lake Park 3 miles west of Troutdale. This family-friendly park as picnic areas, restrooms, walking trail, and ramp for small boats. Park is maintained by Multnomah County.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, brown bullhead, black crappie, bluegill.<br> <br> Blue Lake Regional Park (http://www.oregonmetro.gov/index.cfm/go/by.web/id=149)<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=BLUE+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
