      <Placemark>
        <name>Breitenbush River - Cleator Bend Campground</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4d-Q79-AUBAAEi0RRODO3ssSH7tCLYcIU2MPjgWpPW0LcZ_JRDleZXoM11DOShbMM0YZOariJmdM6K-LwEt8aMky5D5p1hXezKWIiXsgI5eRHiizzFTb0bWf7tMTPtp4qNIwOUEItMhp5K84BNEr_5sDGjAP-XzfxeAij_RqiEICAeDw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This small group campground is located on a bend in the Breitenbush River. From Detroit, go 9 miles east on Breitenbush Road #46; campground is in a wooded area and has nine campsites. Open May-September, maximum stay is 14 days. Fee. Amenities include restrooms,picnic tables, drinking water and fire grills. The Breitenbush River runs through a beautiful, narrow canyon with crystal clear water.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=BREITENBUSH+R&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4d-Q79-AUBAAEi0RRODO3ssSH7tCLYcIU2MPjgWpPW0LcZ_JRDleZXoM11DOShbMM0YZOariJmdM6K-LwEt8aMky5D5p1hXezKWIiXsgI5eRHiizzFTb0bWf7tMTPtp4qNIwOUEItMhp5K84BNEr_5sDGjAP-XzfxeAij_RqiEICAeDw</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.999569,44.777692,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Buck Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6RfRdwfVGr_LfEGkS7iBLfhnXdkaqfKxgV43qzdZ_O401wS4y4WEq9oWRpdrqugnNAhyV2v9ftPgq0nulZHMVcS5Ympl6m2An-2GzSG9H9RjBzKXmxe6oizHwIMY1BzVS2ewqJX-K91ONkLrZ9Lw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>A 5-acre lake about 4.5 miles north of Florence, Ore.. A trail on the west side of Hwy. 101 leads a few hundred feet to the lake.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=buck&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
