      <Placemark>
        <name>Commonwealth Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ZjlfvaafkzHHABM0lxXSxL2-xSn4bLiQfZMAbmTJkkggXNDbgIPCwDD2P3cG2ZgwOQTgGNFBCbwZZf_k27tvPI_d--nBhfTj8jJlQGEqXU6RDpjeDlsbiOfvuymPlCn0Av1WirNxiNZQx5fHUY-nLmwX6JU1q" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a three-acre stocked lake within the Commonwealth Lake Park (http://www.thprd.org/parks/parkdetail.cfm?id=53) in Beaverton. Commonwealth Park is maintained by Tualatin Hills Park and Rec. Amenities (http://www.thprd.org/parks/parkdetail.cfm?id=53) include ADA accessible trail, picnic tables, playground, restrooms. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, bass, bluegill, crappie<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - ttps://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=COMMONWEALTH+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
