      <Placemark>
        <name>Cullaby Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7jJKbdDyodMhUyFzWo2wQQ3T_ZsrOYYZRT1F-LONHxF4TOPgQQZTsYzqDg-m-NoGCOYM7HkA3R21kYzsNXvAUAXzVFyWteI62sCblr2ZZw37Zr6bcdlRpV7DLi4JWj4ofe2HNOTJNwzE-o4hv-e9cB4A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>A 200-acre lake located appr. 4 miles north of Gearhart, Ore., and east of Hwy 101.<br><br>Cullaby Lake County Park  has 165 acres, offering public access to Cullaby Lake boat launch and docks, four-stall flush restrooms, picnic shelters, barbecue pits, and horseshoe pits. Activities include fishing, swimming, wildlife viewing of beavers, bald eagles, deer, and waterfowl.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, white crappie, black crappie, yellow perch, largemouth bass, brown bullhead<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=CULLABY+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
