      <Placemark>
        <name>Detroit Lake - Hoover Campground</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7JItw5NrRnhQ5rczXhjVI_3PoFEUeusyHnLKiYYh5ZhZkceLz5NmZAZZdNbx_PykXPJS67sMUohsLG3nplq8RS67315eDvkPio0A1xiyY8WRH5cp1L28O7fz9Stcl3OxC83-wvc3uhECyq_S8NEObqwdG14T38WUQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Hoover Campground rests at an elevation of 1,600 feet on the shores of Detroit Lake. Camp sites are surrounded by towering trees, making for secluded camping spots. <br><br>There are several hiking trails in the area, including Stahlman Point Trail, which offers beautiful vistas of the lake and surrounding mountain area. There is a boat ramp adjacent to the campground . Additional amenities include: ADA fishing platform, camp sites, vault toilet, grills, paved parking lot. <br><br>Reservations are available  May through September.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=DETROIT+RES&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
