      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Devil's Lake]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4AOmp0P6jChSZJfhlXLqoOdk1PwyFYchVtLmANQaQHjRn9I9lQguzw5LMJR3cXzE4AKQvR08OG4JRLAyo5ouoA-T-0daaurBWxJ1EihryT7VqrKpijpLm_c5mpfPYwYWF6rh1f1uDXXvEwLspWN8kZ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Devils Lake is a 680-acre lake located located on the central Oregon Coast by Lincoln City. The lake connects to the Pacific Ocean by the D River, once considered the shortest in the world. To the east of the lake is the Siuslaw National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/siuslaw). <br><br>This lake is appr. 3 miles long and 1/2 mile wide, with an average depth of 10 feet and a maximum depth of 22 feet. <br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br><br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=3&field_waterbody_name_value_1=dev&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
