      <Placemark>
        <name>Eckman Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5YotHUiLRqNpl9P3g5L6G6eZzu5z_7H6TEYnSkYnp7hemI-ZxNjQNr2qBwyCZeUUqdgWj0yAY-zBaxjLzQDXvWcN6k_2CT2hukwXhcgd11skYLWWo76B4h7ow3KT1DbV7I8Tb7K_wfeFmWsxs2k1k" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Thisis a shallow lake about two miles from Waldport, Ore., that drains into the upper Alsea Bay along Hwy 34. The main fish species to be caught are the stocked rainbow trout, native cutthroat trout and the occasional largemouth bass. The shoreline is in private ownership, except for W. B. Nelson State Recreation Area, which provides picnic areas and restrooms on site.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=ECKMAN+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31- ]]></description>
