      <Placemark>
        <name>EE Wilson Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7RZi_xynI7YrvJE_-XQ4kGkslwP7GShOcH1uWsWj1OfH75yV7JBRnyVwhw31TZugevwRGe1CZYgRt6FGbyInoGD-PbGGv40vYPVFYN8SxHc2iaR-NdVzIaXY2wNqjjm7KWNdebHHZj8lgZLZ2TqHrakYpD" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>A small angling pond located in the EE Wilson Wildlife Area just off Hwy. 99W between Corvallis and Monmouth. The wildlife area is owned and managed by the Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife.<br> <br>Address: 29555 Camp Adair Road<br>Monmouth, OR 97361, Ph. (541) 745-5334 <br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>Wildlife Area Map <br> (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/maps/wildlife_areas/EEwilson_features.pdf)<br>More information (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/ee_wilson_wildlife_area/index.asp)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=EE+WILSON+PD&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
