      <Placemark>
        <name>Elbow Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v58TfKNNE_AtrXjFkodEPj3bhIVZvD-ApTx3TNHvQi8Loh6JCCwS6odEvRVQTAHDmVCOtXWX93xVylULKgkz209iBWeXb9tHvIh7a9zRvL0DIMttbwdXNAIlAcMrOKtYo2bvh9fSd3woqzn62U5jaQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Elbow Lake is a scenic gem of a lake visible from Hwy. 101. It is easily accessible and is equipped with a small boat ramp. The brushy shoreline makes bank angling difficult but rafts, float tubes and cartop boats are popular. Camping is located nearby at Tahkenitch Lake. Tahkenitch Landing Campground (https://fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72BTJw8jAwjQL8h2VAQAzHJMsQ!!/?ss=110612&ttype=recarea&recid=42587&actid=42&navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&position=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&cid=null&pname=Oregon+Dunes+National+Recreation+Area+-+Tahkenitch+Landing+Campground) has 36 tent/trailer sites, water, and flush toilets.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, perch<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=ELBOW+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v58TfKNNE_AtrXjFkodEPj3bhIVZvD-ApTx3TNHvQi8Loh6JCCwS6odEvRVQTAHDmVCOtXWX93xVylULKgkz209iBWeXb9tHvIh7a9zRvL0DIMttbwdXNAIlAcMrOKtYo2bvh9fSd3woqzn62U5jaQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
