      <Placemark>
        <name>Faraday Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7JAcohqAih-9VFWP1fuPuGlj_JUYUOPywgAmt_FqK9xaOoyNEYMABqilAOa0zWwKdQgR-xoq_FvRs94X5tZ16TAi8600MWeTJBsrbygLCQjaI39ezLEkyaL_-oUrZ1FZ_P1hCmv27127w0PU2IlSHQ7g" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Stocked 25-acres reservoir provides year-round fishing. Only bank fishing is allowed -- no boats, rafts, tubes. Located 1.1 miles southeast of Estacada off Hwy 224, the lake is south of the highway next to the Portland General Electric Co. NOTE: PGE is planning work on its hydro facilities at Faraday Lake in 2019  so fishing opportunities will be limited.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, steelhead<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=FARADAY+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
