      <Placemark>
        <name>Foster Reservoir - Gedney Cr Boat Ramp</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5I59stgbN8wvyLWHUrGj77D8i4ff7zYg5eUNiSXnZWkzILpJ9LBHXM_cOu_OFaZePFgnI4bPtV_vbiohAZ6_WixU2ZPZqtLhMIzHT4I7qoinqCEfc8F8j-44Ace5IBX1witgAA7G2AK07xbzEeOwDgwkS-B20MjPZdAyTZ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Gedney Creek Park on Foster Reservoir is operated by the Linn County Parks and Recreation Department (http://www.co.linn.or.us/parks/parks/gedneycreek.html). It is located at 43795 North River Drive, on the north shore of the reservoir approximately one mile east of Foster Dam. Open year-round, facilities include a paved boat ramp, dock, and parking spaces for 55 boats.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, kokanee, bass<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=FOSTER+RES&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
