            -121.959229,45.072187,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Hartman Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Stocked pond is a year-round warmwater and spring trout fishing pond in the Columbia River Gorge. Excellent for non-boating anglers. From I-84, take the Benson State Park exit. The pond is adjacent to the Columbia River adjoining Benson State Recreation Area (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_147.php). <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, bass, crappie, perch <br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=HARTMAN+PD+%28WAHKEENA+LK%29&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.131791,45.576997,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Hebo Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Hebo Lake is about two acres in size and is fairly shallow. A gravel trail around the lake provides good bank access. There are four ADA barrier-free fishing platforms; two are accessible from the paved road. Only non-motorized boats are permitted on the lake, which is better suited to canoes, small rafts or float tubes. The lake is located near several popular hiking trails.<br> <br>Amenities: Day use area with picnic tables and restrooms, campground with 15 sites. <br> <br>Nearby state parks: Bob Straub State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_183.php), Cape Kiwanda State Natural Area (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_180.php), Clay Myers State Natural Area (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_248.php).<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>Hebo Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72BTJw8jAwjQL8h2VAQAzHJMsQ!!/?navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&recid=42705&actid=&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&ss=110612&position=&ttype=recarea&pname=Siuslaw%20National%20Forest%20-%20Hebo%20Lake%20Campground)<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=HEBO+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.797164,45.231322,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Henry Hagg Lake County Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6JS6ft9jb-M5kLlQODuSaH2s0MZ9btIGYnisBhTVxHTyGOwgcATbkONgXwgktdJBvc1RccBaaYTr2wtgEIjX4KIPbwpeio-nGOVFyGADIvctg6Bu1DYlwFK6AvHi6z7YxHmqaDSGCdla3SEFIOlBEDEHniUg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 1,110-acre lake seven miles southwest of Forest Grove. Maintained and operated by Washington County, the park features numerous picnic areas, two boat launching facilities, more than 15 miles of hiking trails, and observation decks for wildlife and bird watching.<br> <br>The park, and access to the lake, is now open year-around.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, smallmouth bass, yellow perch, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead, yellow bullhead, native cutthroat trout.<br> <br>Henry Hagg Lake website (https://www.washcoparks.org/scoggins-valley-park)<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=HENRY+HAGG+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
