        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.938699,45.627394,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Leaburg Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Leaburg Lake is located directly behind Leaburg Dam on the McKenzie River approximately 17 miles east of Springfield on Highway 126 East. <br><br>The Eugene Water & Electric Board Park (http://eweb.org/recreation) at Leaburg Lake offers 55 acres of grounds and facilities that can accommodate small family picnics as well as large groups of up to 600. <br><br>Located at milepost 23.5 of the McKenzie Highway, the park offers modern picnic facilities with free electric stoves, softball diamonds, volleyball court, and a horseshoe pit.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout <br><br>Leaburg Fish Hatchery (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/leaburg_hatchery.asp)<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=LEABURG+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.60931,44.139472,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Loren's Pond]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Small pond located about 1/4 mile west of the Trask Fish Hatchery (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/trask_river_hatchery.asp). <br><br>The pond is located next to the Trask River and a primitive boat ramp giving drift boats access to the lower section of the river, a popular salmon and steelhead fishing area.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, surplus hatchery steelhead when available<br> <br>Trout Stocking schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=LOREN%27S+POND&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.738456,45.434622,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lost Lake - Clatsop County</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5ObntCvXKemYaVEPIb3o4SR9KyFi6_YSBj19x0dqGDWmccfU07M9ajsoo3plN-00WIORPzxxydDx97NCjj5n-DoM4JsJwUciZbfjXuaPrv_xGfggibATGZzHfq-CGTsQQoISnR1J9FAlsZ-2tNBw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Lost Lake is located in a forested setting in the Coast Range Mountains west of Hwy. 26 in the Nehalem River basin. The lake is relatively small, about 15 acres. Some camping is available, but no improved facilities exist. The lake offers public bank access around the entire lake. A boat launch is available for small boats. <br><br>Alternate Activities: Good opportunities for wildlife viewing, particularly deer and elk. The Nehalem River is nearby, offering steelhead fishing in the spring and sea-run cutthroat fishing in the summer. Nearby state parks: Nehalem Bay State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_201.php), Oswald West State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_195.php). <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, surplus hatchery steelhead when available<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=LOST+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5ObntCvXKemYaVEPIb3o4SR9KyFi6_YSBj19x0dqGDWmccfU07M9ajsoo3plN-00WIORPzxxydDx97NCjj5n-DoM4JsJwUciZbfjXuaPrv_xGfggibATGZzHfq-CGTsQQoISnR1J9FAlsZ-2tNBw</value>
          </Data>
