      <Placemark>
        <name>Mercer Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v58EZrlIeE5PGHLSfPe6YIwuSJesAC9ghImi8Txg0y-fSwRpp4jlsXPPef6KSTdqgXDJoev8S5Nuqj-IHz0dvuSFtm8y00QnJrHZm3vQnHYAxS5dEc9s5INKh7oO61sWwU928dWPv_foTekg4O5bovh" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Mercer Lake is a 340--acre lake located about 5 miles north of Florence east of Hwy 101. The lake is open year round. It has 11 miles of shoreline and is accessible both by boat and from the shore. The lake has an average depth of 30 feet deep, with summer temperatures around 70 degrees. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch, bluegill <br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=MERCER+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
