      <Placemark>
        <name>Munsel Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6i9hofOdUt1Sh6kT9d9RdbY1uTlU7gFoZd2sqn24KOPeMTpq9CF14HlG1Lt6U3C0LvTxP9y2xVhEKDQ_NkRbRqdCNTpBzhGFfAlURrPXMKjg-coY-lp4saMBMzybdons1Af2k405jbObvfCIuqkoWb" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Munsel Lake is a 104-acre lake located about 1.5 miles north of Florence, Ore., east of Hwy 101. This lake ranges in depth from 4 to 10 ft. and serves as an important recreational use area for boating, swimming and fishing. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch, bluegill<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=MUNSEL+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-02-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
