      <Placemark>
        <name>North Fork Reservoir Site #1</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4-LcC7Zah3SrjQ3Pl6ZucH5GsRMGBEaJinY3fDMqKEXR1XKFKYtUZQsvycsJnDLBzLanxvQm_vjeVMhm-joz_srarZQ14EbpP8Gjearx-3tyMVJH-zU7Dr6pFCevukvh51NEMmILJWCwYPabLX5r-qqQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 350-acre reservoir of the Clackamas River behind North Fork Dam approximately 5.2 miles east of Estacada, Ore.. This stocking site is sourth of Hwy. 224 and has an ADA accessible fishing dock. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, salmon, steelhead<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=NORTH+FORK+RES&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
