      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>North Fork Reservoir - Promotory Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6lJK9BY_RpmME8NVLakikCTtOeA6hPAKQrU1uskQ5lQPHz-GQrufBy5lXiuV_1uKl1NlX-CNlOc1muCArWO__opR-B7D62P2n3YF6sIlHDEanmC9LD4zDb1MuUmv0NwICpIEb-CqHqQbY8w4_ZV71KJ60oxNIlTNA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Promotory Park is the largest and most developed of three sites on North Fork Reservoir where ODFW releases rainbow trout.This park has a boat ramp, boat moorage, 50 campsites, picnic areas, electric cooking facilities, boat rentals, grocery store, and ADA-accessible fishing platform.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, salmon, steelhead <br><br> <br>Youth fishing: Just a few hundred yards from North Fork Reservoir at Promotory Campground is Small Fry Lake. This one-acre lake was developed for the exclusive use of young anglers. Kids up to 17 years old can fish for their limit of two fish per day.<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=NORTH+FORK+RES&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
