      <Placemark>
        <name>Olalla Creek Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v75vA6dub0kkziIBPeKdXYaz3HyurZ4q3o4iwXkVJUNoBXT30Xmdce9Elfv1kbBNXpKzUZmuuPYy7tiQZSGHButR3q1b5zDu5b7AlpoNXMwqPXwNIw_t3SLAP0Tv6JOsoqrV73Bwl0Ll_xv6fH0-9vatid8uYqf5qS1cWA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Olalla Creek Reservoir is a 120-acre reservoir on Olalla Creek about a mile north of Toledo, Ore. The reservoir reaches a maximum depth of about 65 feet near Olalla dam. The shoreline and much of the surrounding landscape is owned by Georgia Pacific Corporation and managed as commercial timberland. The company allows public access to the water, and small boats without motors may be launched. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout <br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=OLALLA+CR+RESERVOIR&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
