      <Placemark>
        <name>Quartzville Creek - Boulder Cr. Bridge</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4MKdy_VA8hORtWLsWsDfZ3FT2DG9ekS73i5A9kF_02ELrtuy-NJ81yEqoyqZEKSf2F3tbY8QlhzX9c12o-6FNEGVyoCoCBZhq3k2jwK4yrPvYdkizzDaRS25g1UdYKOB_kOLpMZbDiyidCJLuxzkbTWW0Gxtmg-uNQhYY" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Quartzville Creek is a wild and scenic river extending 12 miles upstream from Green Peter Reservoir to the Willamette National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/willamette) boundry. It offers a variety of recreational opportunities such as gold panning, fishing, camping and high-flow kayaking. The Quartzville Back Country Byway (http://www.blm.gov/or/resources/recreation/files/brochures/quartzville_110119.pdf) parallels the winding river, offering views of old-growth forests and wildlife and providing easy access to developed and undeveloped picnic and camping sites.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=QUARTZVILLE+CR&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
