      <Placemark>
        <name>Roaring River Park Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5IYzI9axh8wn6GUCFadqKj51YqT9F7elgm6wENYfxEpeqMASNRs0p7lPlMEEQMFxTELN8k1brWFYKJW_lU4yEnzTPlfzXzcuIf22cGhBu7QSgTA4Dm2rsv9xk0xscEi7P4FVcKdqvXphV3xatxGqJJUeLUl2N0fA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>A small pond in a day-use park near ODFW's Roaring River Fish Hatchery. <br>Roaring River is one of ODFW's primary trout rearing facilities. It has an outdoor display board, fish viewing pond.<br> <br>Not currently stocked<br><br>More information (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/roaring_river_hatchery.asp)<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5IYzI9axh8wn6GUCFadqKj51YqT9F7elgm6wENYfxEpeqMASNRs0p7lPlMEEQMFxTELN8k1brWFYKJW_lU4yEnzTPlfzXzcuIf22cGhBu7QSgTA4Dm2rsv9xk0xscEi7P4FVcKdqvXphV3xatxGqJJUeLUl2N0fA</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.717122,44.624476,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Salish Pond -West</name>
        <description><![CDATA[One of two ponds located in the 70-acre Salish Ponds Wetlands Park in Fairview, Ore. The 6-acre west pond is regularly stocked with rainbow trout. It also contains warmwater fish. The east pond is stocked periodically with warmater fish transplanted by the Oregon Bass and Panfish Club. Boats and swimming are not allowed.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, crappie, bass, catfish. <br><br>Facilities: restrooms, nature trail, disabled accessible docks at both ponds, nearby stores that supply fishing gear. <br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SALISH+PD%2C+WEST&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-02-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.449708,45.529832,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Salmonberry Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Srpb1mid2_UXtc3RnQvWUozFY_2XjXgZbBFe7btuktpSP6gYoLMWJbdScQyuTlTI138ARu06-VRUHBlWY-vyrXRdSneZ6_Rthsh3MNFtz9kztwl9x7__PyADsCRpxBLOTKBf82JSWyT0YpkdfALXRWylLgrw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Salmonberry Lake is owned by the city of St. Helens and is about three acres in size. It is a former municipal water supply secluded in the woods off of Pittsburgh Road. The road to the pond is gated and anglers must walk about 1/3 mile to access this pond. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, sunfish<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SALMONBERRY+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Srpb1mid2_UXtc3RnQvWUozFY_2XjXgZbBFe7btuktpSP6gYoLMWJbdScQyuTlTI138ARu06-VRUHBlWY-vyrXRdSneZ6_Rthsh3MNFtz9kztwl9x7__PyADsCRpxBLOTKBf82JSWyT0YpkdfALXRWylLgrw</value>
