      <Placemark>
        <name>Siltcoos Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v782vxqnK2e4018zbgTY7Urs9CG582Z3eU_1IcDGyrRmeK3Xi4Hm6MMAloU9HxjJjk4tpaqxXUkipnyRTQpS76NLzAqrwDZHvjNyzdyvU-I2lsAIs8cawbZtL-8W6-QdsGAJ8mTnYZb6ze9UF_R2yLfedk" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Siltcoos Lake, at 3,164 acres in size, is the largest lake on the central Oregon Coast. The lake is very popular for boating and fishing. The shoreline tends to be brushy and mostly in private ownership. For this reason, fishing from boats is prefered by most anglers. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch, crappie, bluegill, bullhead<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SILTCOOS+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-10-31]]></description>
