          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Smith Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 35-acre lake located less than 2 miles north of Garibaldi, Ore., on Hwy. 101. Private land surrounds most of this lake. Bank access is limited from the highway side and requires a short walk over uneven terrain. Stocking is done at the dock located at Camp Magruder. It is possible to slide a small boat into the lake at a road crossing on the north end. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch, bluegill<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SMITH+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.949492,45.578454,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Smith Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Reservoir on the Willamette National Forest appr. 70 miles east of Springfield, Ore., This reservoir spans 170 acres and is part of the Carmen-Smith Hydroelectric Project, owned by the Eugene Water & Electric Board. Smith complex offers camping, picknicking and a boat launch maintained by the U.S. Forest Service.<br> The Eugene Water & Electric Board is conducting a five-year construction project to retrofit, refurbish and upgrade capital equipment at its Carmen-Smith Hydroelectric Project. The work is being conducted in anticipation of a new federal operating license for the project.<br><br>The capital construction projects planned for the 2017-2021 time frame will create significant public access constraints due primarily to safety concerns. In order to keep the public and construction personnel safe during the five-year project, EWEB and the Forest Service agreed to close access to Forest Road 730 at the Powerhouse. The closure will deny public access to Trail Bridge Campground, Smith Reservoir and Lake’s End Campground. The closure of the road to the public will begin in March 2017 and continue through 2021.<br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, eastern brook trout<br><br><br>More information (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/willamette/recreation/recarea/?recid=4400)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SMITH+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.045692,44.30676,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>South Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[A 5-acre lake located within the Siuslaw National Forest. This lake is located on the ridgeline above Hebo Lake. Next to the lake is a U.S. Forest Service campground that is open year around. The last several miles of road to the lake are unimproved and rough. Use caution on this road. It is not advisable to take trailers to this lake.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br><br>South Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72BTJw8jAwjQL8h2VAQAzHJMsQ!!/?ss=110612&ttype=recarea&recid=42715&actid=79&navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&position=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&navid=110400000000000&pnavid=110000000000000&cid=null&pname=Mt.+Hebo+Area+-+South+Lake+Campground)<br> <br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=SOUTH+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.721504,45.202603,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>South Yamhill River</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7HtnG15ykf7ktsjOc4Sx2KffBSduRYlfZOKtfzTRFh1_vQSmBFWov6BIj_a5WQIY9pydFGe2YiuySGqJIjgqBq0sRiyaqFXngtnO4vvooIHsnaucG_DerNL_bqkwnKZz2PxyRT0pM4gEh5zOqwCQLGzxNYpFSl6Mo" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The South Fork Yamhill from its confluence with the North Yamhill near McMinnville, upstream about 20 miles to Rock Creek near Grand Ronde is stocked with rainbow trout. <br> <br>Trout are released in multiple locations between Gold Creek Road Bridge and Willamina.Yamhill River Road runs parallel to much of this section and provides adequate turnouts and parking at several locations near the river. The remaining 15 miles of river open to trout fishing has some public access but also meanders across private lands. ODFW reminds anglers to be aware of and respectful toward private property rights along the river.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=YAMHILL+R&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7HtnG15ykf7ktsjOc4Sx2KffBSduRYlfZOKtfzTRFh1_vQSmBFWov6BIj_a5WQIY9pydFGe2YiuySGqJIjgqBq0sRiyaqFXngtnO4vvooIHsnaucG_DerNL_bqkwnKZz2PxyRT0pM4gEh5zOqwCQLGzxNYpFSl6Mo</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
