      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Tahoe Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tahoe Lake is accessible via forest roads in the Coast Range east of Tillamook. The lake offers public bank access around the entire lake on an unimproved trail. An unimproved boat launch is available for small boats. No ADA facilities or restrooms.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, surplus hatchery steelhead when available<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=TAHOE+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.600955,45.350064,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Thissel Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7RbUN5UjDpjFFqWRJuEJ3-jKeXbw50anBjL2G7syelsC23BszwHVDs_Alt2kI9pgcdEHFsg3Ja4tEZpXbXXtZURU4B5k8C9IgBIN36sCc6tV9M1KcBczff7CLOoewoaW33qknv_oa-15h_voLI_iVk" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 3-acre pond located just downstream from ODFW's Oregon Hatchery Research Center (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/fish/OHRC/) along Fall Creek. This pond dries up around mid-summer but supports a stocked rainbow trout fishery during the winter/spring season.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule -https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=THISSEL+PD&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31 ]]></description>
