      <Placemark>
        <name>Timber Linn Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v40EfmS1wyqknXZkxiZYN4WCK8iSSmE4yKpLjyvPYSAxrYFG40_Glz8aMicEILsd-6JSIZgAflswKv66IpAiv0oPMXxhnheYXQONhCfRAnfjTBW_vyqv_dz68AKO4a1fIbSXwWRW2lT-I3inMW5dQGZODZhreQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is an 11-acre pond in the 90-acre Timber Linn Memorial Park in Albany, Ore. This is a good lake for inexperience anglers because of easy access to the water. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, white crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead, largemouth bass <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule - https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=TIMBER+LINN+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
