      <Placemark>
        <name>Timothy Lake - Gone Creek Campground</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5EL0T2Ot04HraG1ixyZQnnA2kte4Rqjqg4SJH5_VuD5FDvHOn1sLkPYRzMpyLI16lT_MyROKanCxzmgIkv8OW5FSKhG4XoAs3h3TGqRqegipnEbKT4O7EMJ-KND0lqJzgq18yW8LFlODgL7YY8O1FTjMfakgPl" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Timothy Lake is one of the most popular family camping and fishing destinations in the Mt. Hood National Forest. The lake's south shore features four developed campgrounds and boat ramps. Three smaller, less developed campgrounds are found in the north. A trail system for hikers, mountain bikers and equestrians circles the lake. The Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail also traverses the area along the east side of the lake. Motorboats are allowed on Timothy Lake, although a 10 m.p.h. speed limit is in place. <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, kokanee, eastern brook, cutthroat trout, crayfish. Anglers are asked to identify their catch and are encouraged to release native cutthroat trout unharmed.<br>Lat./Long. Coordinates: 45.113633,-121.773577<br>STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=Timothy&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5EL0T2Ot04HraG1ixyZQnnA2kte4Rqjqg4SJH5_VuD5FDvHOn1sLkPYRzMpyLI16lT_MyROKanCxzmgIkv8OW5FSKhG4XoAs3h3TGqRqegipnEbKT4O7EMJ-KND0lqJzgq18yW8LFlODgL7YY8O1FTjMfakgPl</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.773577,45.113633,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Timothy Lake - Hoodview Campground</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4UYqvA_gXFJVPjX33vr128V4LdHD8N7vtTPNfeR-CL0bOsJgD_ZNh0gYIKUk49X5oyRQKSWwKjgu6Tzh2T6eXiVDh5CjvLm7VeGhiRRr_142DgU88Xc9YkYbHcalsppEOCJvaNt4FSqWCI28DvKb-CPxWKsUgp" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Timothy Lake is one of the most popular family camping and fishing destinations in the Mt. Hood National Forest. The lake's south shore features four developed campgrounds and boat ramps. Three smaller, less developed campgrounds are found in the north. A trail system for hikers, mountain bikers and equestrians circles the lake. The Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail also traverses the area along the east side of the lake. Motorboats are allowed on Timothy Lake, although a 10 m.p.h. speed limit is in place. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, kokanee, eastern brook, cutthroat trout, crayfish. Anglers are asked to identify their catch and are encouraged to release native cutthroat trout unharmed.<br>STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=Timothy&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
