      <Placemark>
        <name>Town Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 9-acre impoundement located near the community of Woods, Ore. Most of the lake is surrounded by private land but public access is available along the west shore near the boat ramp, and includes the boat ramp itself. The bank to the lake is steep and brushy. An angling dock is located on the west side of the lake and is accessible by steep, unimproved trails that must be used with extreme caution.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, surplus hatchery steelhead when available<br> <br>STOCKING SCHEDULE --https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=TOWN+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.955994,45.224551,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Trail Bridge Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 120-acre reservoir about an hour east of Eugene, Oregon on Hwy. 126, within the Willamette National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/willamette). The reservoir has 46 walk-in/tent sites and 19 RV sites (without hookups), paved access roads, gravel boat launch, fishing platform, picnic tables, fire rings and one seasonal restroom. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/willamette-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.048664,44.276425,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Trillium Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4qYaKcocXLJlvRqnL0TdQ0is49es1WsrBVtJgfAT5ypejOnkiiqu5rYmxBK62kaiSlE6NzWfU5dT9zWbMRnGEaoYlflo8gPxxGICjNptYnj4SEiIg6TiFn2LMi9DkAdox06qOH5-qBWGY6KxphMyarB4k" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Trillium is a 60-acre lake located appr. three miles east of Government Camp off of Hwy 26. This lake is popular for fishing, camping and photography, often clearly reflecting Mount Hood. Adjacent Trillium Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/mthood/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=53634&actid=29) is administered by the Zigzag Ranger District of the Mount Hood National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/mthood/). The large campground features a seasonal boat ramp and wheelchair-accessible floating dock. <br>STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=TRILLIUM+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
