            -122.890706,46.036524,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Vernonia Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6bBkGq5UodRJBDSwdBXQDGV1_17go5CjOKZn9NMMGsPzzHNJDOEijE5UlAuU2RF1sMy2wE3LlVXZ2t0XLP3lFNYRFzqRutR6KlzpcXpel1iAOegdu1NiHXgc7WRSvw8Xy-SbLY_kXlJsQRWWdm58BdaVk" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Located at the north end of Vernonia, Ore., on Hwy 47, this waterbody was once the mill pond of the Oregon-American Lumber Company. <br>Amenities: Primitive/walk-in camping area with fire pits, restrooms, drinking water, boat ramp (gas powered motors are not allowed), ADA wheelchair accessible fishing docks and restrooms, bank fishing access, and children’s playground area. There is an on-site bait shop during the spring and summer months. The Banks-Vernonia bike trail starts and ends at this site. Fishing is best in spring, as warmer temperatures promote growth of aquatic vegetation. The city of Vernonia owns this pond and charges $5 to park at the site.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead, surplus hatchery steelhead. STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=VERNONIA+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6bBkGq5UodRJBDSwdBXQDGV1_17go5CjOKZn9NMMGsPzzHNJDOEijE5UlAuU2RF1sMy2wE3LlVXZ2t0XLP3lFNYRFzqRutR6KlzpcXpel1iAOegdu1NiHXgc7WRSvw8Xy-SbLY_kXlJsQRWWdm58BdaVk</value>
          </Data>
