      <Placemark>
        <name>Walter Wirth Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7UMpq6sLHA56tm_RIOQKT9zKAXt4hAfV4myyl2PyxFWEagj8E26DY4ZrrPpDEafqgYKnIe3xtpIp8qRcpGYCuaHklYOqp9nX_Lb01daYiKpJg5m3bX7XoeB2zHUVR5mik4rqq6h6yLa9YA1-Dn8RNpOwg-mZ8" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Walter Wirth Lake is a 20-acre pond located within the City of Salem's Cascades Gateway Park. The lake is named after Walter L. Wirth, a park superintendent for the City of Salem Parks Department from 1954-1958. <br>Mill Stream, which runs through the park, has become a spawning area for fall Chinook salmon. <br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill, brown bullhead, channel catfish, white crappie<br> <br>STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=WALTER+WIRTH+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7UMpq6sLHA56tm_RIOQKT9zKAXt4hAfV4myyl2PyxFWEagj8E26DY4ZrrPpDEafqgYKnIe3xtpIp8qRcpGYCuaHklYOqp9nX_Lb01daYiKpJg5m3bX7XoeB2zHUVR5mik4rqq6h6yLa9YA1-Dn8RNpOwg-mZ8</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.99,44.91,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Waverly Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7hkqJSc1WUkqxnOaAUWbWRdM_RMfH8bUFbaogvvDEIpffrPe_E3dPAVNYdrQA_7y9yW6NTsrmNuE4QPrQXAq-su6Sn1HSBdAMK7ysICSzqn9Rlpk5hzjjF104ICaqdpVNFjL0-A7ZXSOLy73CONG6K2g" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Waverly Lake is is located in an Albany City Park with restrooms and picnic facilities. In the summer months, paddle boats are available for rent.Other recreational activities are available nearby including paved bike trails, hiking and wildlife viewing. Waverly Lake offers excellent bank fishing opportunities and also has good access for disabled anglers, including a dock. There is a paved trail around the entire lake. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, blue catfish, brown trout, crappie, largemouth bass<br><br>STOCKING SCHEDULE -- https://myodfw.com/fishing/species/trout/stocking-schedule?field_zone_value=All&field_waterbody_name_value_1=WAVERLY+LK&field_planned_stocking_date_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-01-01&field_planned_stocking_date_end_value%5Bdate%5D=2019-12-31]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7hkqJSc1WUkqxnOaAUWbWRdM_RMfH8bUFbaogvvDEIpffrPe_E3dPAVNYdrQA_7y9yW6NTsrmNuE4QPrQXAq-su6Sn1HSBdAMK7ysICSzqn9Rlpk5hzjjF104ICaqdpVNFjL0-A7ZXSOLy73CONG6K2g</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
