          <Data name="AccessDirections">
            <value>T23S, R5-1/2E, Sec 2 
43.6019144N   122.1011897W

2006:  Hike-in lake, 1 mile in Willamette National Forest. From Eugene, take Hwy 58 east to Odell Lake. From West Bay on the lake, take Forest Rd. 5899 which parallels the railroad to the old station of Abernethy. Take Deer Creek Trail 3670 south. (Oregon Fish Finder)

2011:  From Abernathy SnoPark, follow dirt road and turn right on Spur Rd 501.  Keep right at split.  Travel 3.0 miles to end of road at Deer Ck.  Trail head is across Deer Ck near railroad.  Old trail head appeared to have crossed no-longer-existing bridge across Deer Ck upstream of end of road.   A mile-long developed Forest Service trail climbs uphill to Lower and Upper Abernathy Lakes from the end of the road. </value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="MaximumDepth">
            <value><![CDATA[20']]></value>
          </Data>
