43.9890363N   121.8742391W

2012:  A 3-acre lake located in the Three Sisters Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Bend, take the Cascade Lakes Highway (Hwy 46) west to Elk Lake.  The Island Meadows Trailhead is across from the Ranger Station at the north end of Elk Lake. From Island Meadows Trailhead, continue west to the Pacific Crest Trail. Turn south on the Pacific Crest Trail and continue to junction of USFS Trail 3517.  Continue northwest on USFS Trail 3517 to McBee Trail (USFS Trail 3523); continue northeast (right turn) on USFS Trail 3523 to Herb Lake (located on the right side of the trail).  Aerial Lake is approximately 200 yards southeast of Herb Lake.  Suggest compass and good map. </value>
