        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.1573857<br>Latitude: 43.4595055<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T24S, R5E, Sec 25<br>43.4595055N   122.1573857W<br><br>1989:  Two miles west of Summit Lake immediately north of Emigrant Butte.  No trail to lake or identifying sign.  Hike 300 yards up a dry (or nearly dry) small creek channel to the lake from Forest Service Road 391 at a point 0.3 mile south of its junction with Road 380.  (Don't confuse with a larger creek just 0.1 mile from this junction.)  An alternate route of about the same hiking distance can be taken downhill from Forest Service Road 393 south of the lake.  <br>MaximumDepth: 13'<br>Year Stocked: 2018<br>Species: Cutthroat Trout]]></description>
