        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -121.8568715<br>Latitude: 44.1416280<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T16S, R8E, Sec 28<br>44.1416280N   121.8568715W<br><br>2012:  A 2-acre lake located in the Three Sisters Wilderness in Willamette National Forest. From Eugene, take Highway 126 east; turn right on to Foley Ridge Road (USFS Road 2643) and follow USFS Road 2643 to the end.  Take USFS Trail 3511 for approximately 8 miles, then head north on USFS Trail 3547 for 1 mile to reach Eileen Lake.  Amstutz Lake is located about ½ mile northwest of Eileen Lake at the top of the steep, rocky slope overlooking Eileen.   <br>MaximumDepth: 20'<br>Year Stocked: 2019, Natural Production<br>Species: Brook Trout]]></description>
