        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.3230379<br>Latitude: 43.8548344<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T20S, R4E, Sec 3<br>43.8548344N   122.3230379W<br><br>Andrews Lake is a small lake in Section 03 which is shown at the head of Cedar Creek on the Willamette National Forest maps.  However, it is not located on the creek, just in its headwaters, and its winter overflow, if any, probably drains eventually into Cedar Creek.  <br>MaximumDepth: 18'<br>Year Stocked: 2018<br>Species: Cutthroat Trout]]></description>
