        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.0364625<br>Latitude: 43.7796146<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T20S, R6E, Sec 5<br>43.7796146N   122.0364625W<br><br>2012:  A 3-acre lake located in the Three Sisters Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge, follow Highway 58 to the Waldo Lake Road (USFS Road 5897); turn northeast and travel the east side of Waldo Lake;  From North Waldo Campground on the northeast end of the lake, take the Jim Weaver Loop National Recreation Trail (USFS Trail 3590) west; after approximately one mile cut north on USFS Trail 3555 to Lower Rigdon Lake.  Easiest access is to walk northeast from northeast corner of Lower Rigdon Lake (from a point where the shoreline trail leaves the lake shore and heads toward Kiwa Lake) up a steep hill 300 yards to Dan Lake.  A compass and good map are recommended. <br>MaximumDepth: 20'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Brook Trout]]></description>
