        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.1326449<br>Latitude: 43.6857014<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T22S, R5.5E, Sec 4<br>43.6857014N   122.1326449W<br><br>2012:  A 5-acre lake located in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge, travel east on Highway 58; take USFS Road 5883 east to USFS Road 5883-381 (Spur Road 381); continue on USFS Spur Road 381 to road’s end.  Grace Lake is located approximate 3 miles northwest of Mt. Fuji.  No trail or easy access; suggested route is to hike downhill a long mile to the north from the end of USFS Spur Road 381 using a compass and good map.  Steep slopes and dense rhododendron growths to the west and north greatly impede access from those directions.  Grace Lake is tucked up close to a steep hillside immediately to the west. <br>MaximumDepth: 17'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Rainbow Trout]]></description>
