      <Placemark>
        <name>Harvey</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.0366913<br>Latitude: 43.7886128<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T20S, R6.5E, Sec 32 <br>43.7886128N   122.0366913W<br><br>2014:  A 19-acre lake located in the Waldo Lake Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge, follow Highway 58 to the Waldo Lake Road (USFS Road 5897), turning northeast to travel up the east side of Waldo Lake to North Waldo Campground; from North Waldo Campground on the northeast end of Waldo Lake, continue north on dirt road (USFS Road 516) to the Taylor Burn Road (USFS Road 514); continue west on the USFS Road 514 to the Taylor Burn Campground; from Taylor Burn Campground, hike south on the Wahanna Trail (USFS Trail 3583) to Wahanna Lake.  As this trail passes the SW corner of Wahanna Lake it crosses the large and usually dry Wahanna Lake outlet.  After crossing the outlet on the trail, head southwest about 400 yards (bearing 230 degrees), following contours, toward small butte (western shore of Harvey).  If head too sharply west, will run into outlet from Harvey.  There is no trail and lots of downed wood to negotiate through burn.  <br>MaximumDepth: 24'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Rainbow Trout]]></description>
