        <name>Last</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.0986433<br>Latitude: 43.7130373<br>Stock Interval: 1<br>AccessDirections: T21S, R5.5E, Sec 26<br>43.7130373N   122.0986433W<br><br>2012:  An 8-acre lake located in the Waldo Lake Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge take Highway 58 east to Salmon Creek Road (USFS Road 24), continue on USFS Road 24 to junction; turn left onto Black Creek Road (USFS Road 2421).  From USFS Road 2421, travel ½ mile, turn left onto USFS Road 2422 and follow road’s end. There is a trailhead that begins at the end of USFS Road 2422.  From the trailhead, the shortest access is by forging a path through brush for approximately one mile south and slightly west using a compass and a good map; there is no trail or identifying sign.  Last Lake is 400 yards west of Cardiac Lake and near top of steep cliff dropping south toward Black Creek.  <br>MaximumDepth: 15'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Rainbow Trout]]></description>
