      <Placemark>
        <name>Marty</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -121.8349537<br>Latitude: 44.2190269<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T15S, R7.5E, Sec 30<br>44.2190269N   121.8349537W<br><br>1987:  In Three Sisters Wilderness, 0.6 mile southeast of the top of Condon Butte.  No trail directly to lake.  Is a new homemade, wooden "Marty Lake" sign on tree near south shore.  From a signed trailhead on the Old McKenzie Pass Highway near the Scott Lake access road, hike the trail south and uphill about 2-1/2 miles until reaching a large lava flow along the left (north) side of the trail.  Leave the trail here and follow the lava flow about 0.8 mile north to Marty Lake.  <br>MaximumDepth: 10' +<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Brook Trout]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-7C3592-labelson</styleUrl>
