44.2190269N   121.8349537W

1987:  In Three Sisters Wilderness, 0.6 mile southeast of the top of Condon Butte.  No trail directly to lake.  Is a new homemade, wooden "Marty Lake" sign on tree near south shore.  From a signed trailhead on the Old McKenzie Pass Highway near the Scott Lake access road, hike the trail south and uphill about 2-1/2 miles until reaching a large lava flow along the left (north) side of the trail.  Leave the trail here and follow the lava flow about 0.8 mile north to Marty Lake.  ]]></value>
          </Data>
