        <name>Mosquito, Little</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.1940062<br>Latitude: 43.4652601<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T24S, R5E, Sec 27<br>43.4652601N   122.1940062W<br><br>1988:  In upper Middle Fork Willamette River drainage, 1/4 mile east of Forest Service Road 2154.  New logging road spurs approach closed to the lake but it can still be difficult to find; here is one suggested route:  On Road 2154, park at the second wide spot downhill from Spur 383 and hike uphill about 500 yards to the northeast; the lake lies down a steep slope just over the first major rhododendron-covered ridge.  No access trails or identifying signs.  This is not the other lake about a mile southeast in Section 26 identified as Mosquito Lake on some Forest Service maps. <br>MaximumDepth: 7'<br>Year Stocked: 2018<br>Species: Rainbow Trout]]></description>
