        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.1636443<br>Latitude: 43.4695892<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: 24S, R5E, Sec 24<br>43.4695892N   122.1636443W<br>2012:  A 2-acre lake located in the Diamond Peak Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge, take Highway 58 east to Crescent Lake Junction; drive around the northwest shore of Crescent Lake on USFS Road 60 to USFS Road 6010.  Continue west on USFS Road 6010 to Summit Lake Campground; From Summit Campground continue on USFS Road 380 west to Trailhead (north side of road) for USFS Trail 3699;  on USFS Trail 3699,  hike north for .25 mile and then cut west across country to Ruth Lake. From Ruth Lake, Paddock Lake is 0.3 mile west and 150 yards southwest of Neet Lake.  Suggest use of good map and compass.<br>MaximumDepth: 17'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Cutthroat Trout]]></description>
