        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.0229164<br>Latitude: 43.7997368<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T20S, R6E, Sec 33<br>43.7997368N   122.0229164W<br><br>2012:  A 14-acre lake located in the Waldo Lake Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge follow Highway 58 to the Waldo Lake Road (USFS Road 5897); turn northeast and travel east side of Waldo Lake.  From North Waldo Campground on the northeast end of the lake; continue north on USFS Road 516 that meets the Taylor Burn Road (USFS Road 514); continue west on USFS Road 514; The trailhead is located on Taylor Burn Road 100 yards west of the trail into Helen Lake.  Follow the Fields Lake Trail (USFS Trail 3579) south for approximately one mile to Fields Lake; from Fields Lake a well-defined but undeveloped trail drops downhill 300 yards southeast to Whig Lake.  <br>MaximumDepth: 10'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Brook Trout]]></description>
