        <name>Zircon</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Longitude: -122.0799995<br>Latitude: 43.7457634<br>Stock Interval: 2<br>AccessDirections: T21S, R5.5E, Sec 13.   <br> 43.7457634N   122.0799995W                                                                 A 4-acre lake located in the Waldo Lake Wilderness in Willamette National Forest.  From Oakridge, take Highway 58 east to USFS Road 24 (Salmon Creek Road); continue on USFS Road 24 (where it becomes USFS Road 2421); turn left (north) on USFS Road 2422; follow USFS Road 2422 to end and to trailhead; follow USFS Trail 3576 east for approximately 1 mile to Waldo Lake; from Waldo Lake head north on the Jim Weaver Loop National Recreation Trail (USFS Trail 3590) for 2 miles to Elbow Lake.  Zircon Lake is ¾ mile southwest of Elbow Lake and 500 yards east of Sapphire Lake.  No trail or identifying sign (no simple access).  Suggest route is from Elbow Lake using a compass and good map.                <br>MaximumDepth: 33'<br>Year Stocked: 2019<br>Species: Brook Trout]]></description>
